With the different visions that Ryan had it was like J.J. had to go back in TROS and explain everything that could’ve been detailed a lot more. I still love this trilogy it’s just things that you notice a lot and go why didn’t they just stick with that and make a lot more sense? In the end I loved TROS and the characters of this trilogy are amazing but the story really is just everywhere.

1. When the fuck did Palpatine have a child to make the future Rey?
2. Why the fuck were the parents not Siths?

4. Why the fuck did Hux even _ everything?
5. What the fuck is the point of Snoke if Palpatine was alive all this time and Rey was supposed to inherit the throne?
6. How the fuck did Finn just randomly have the 'Force feeling', sensing Rey and everything?
7. Why the fuck couldn't Rey heal Kylo at the end before he died, and why the fuck didn't Rey vanish when she 'died'?
8. What the fuck was that golden lightsaber?
9. Didnt the original Death Star blew up into absolute nothing ? How the fuck is there over half of its star body still holding on together?
10. Is this the actual end of this saga? Or is fucking Palpatine gonna come back at the end of the next trilogy again, if there's any (there's definitely gonna be another one)? Can we finally have new characters that don't have to directly connect to previous characters that have ended the same war like 5 times.

I suspect Snoke was intended to be Darth Plagaus reincarnated. After all he found a way to cheat death. What if his spirit can attach itself to the living world while regenerating his body?

Anyway that plan backfired thanks to Ryan Johnson killing him off like a nobody.

Still, JJ could've made it work. What if Snoke dying allowed Palpatine's spirit to also regenerate his body? Like those two sith Lords were holding each other's spirit hostage. They could even say Palpatine's death in episode 6 was what allowed Plagaus to return in the first place.

Here's how I'd make the films. Have the knights of ren be the main
villains instead of Palpatine or Snoke or even have the first order.
Luke has his Jedi order and Leia is a jedi teacher. Leia has a cyan
lightsaber and Luke still has his green one. Rey is a scavenger and
found that she showed a little force potential when Luke found her
trying to find students. Finn was part of an experiment to create force
sensitive stormtroopers and was very young but the experiment fell after
the empire fell. The knights are Vader fanatics seeking out sith
holocrons that Vader left for a sinister purpose. Kylo has a green
crossguard as the green crystal was gifted by Luke but was cracked when
he damaged it in a fit of rage. I'd remove the bleeding crystal method
as I find it unique if a dark sider has a non red blade and a light
sider has a red blade. Rey has a double bladed purple lightsaber she
constructs, and Finn has a standard blue one. Rey unlike in the movies
we have seen, actually works hard and while she is talented she does
actually get trained before she does the cool stuff. The knights also
have red armored troopers similar to sith troopers as just body guards
as well. Along the way to defeat them, they come across other force
orders that are light sided, dark sided and even gray sided like the
guardians of the breath and imperial knights and they all have their own
agenda and beliefs.


Kylo does reform over time. Rey and Finn fall in love. Also it turns out
that with all the warring factions, a sith lord named Jar Jar was
behind everything as Jar Jar was a partner of Palpatine. Since Palpatine
had an apprentice, Jar Jar laid low hence his absence in later movies
until Palpatine was destroyed and JarJar would continue the rule of two
sith, trying to find other force users to corrupt like Rey. Rey turns
out to be Anakin Skywalker reincarnated. Anakin foresaw a sith lord in
the future and other dark siders and so Anakin gave up immortality to
reincarnate into another body. Hence why she has connections with Luke,
Leia and Kylo and also why Anakin is absent as a ghost and also explains
Rey's power. We'd see scenes of Rey interacting with her previous
incarnation Anakin. Turns out Jar Jar was behind the clone wars, the
empire and the warring factions between other force orders for a
sinister purpose as well and it comes down to Rey and Finn and Kylo
fighting against him, in his throne that looks similar to Palpatine's in
TROS. Jar Jar shoots red force lightning and has a dark core unstable
red lightsaber blade. Rey defeats him and the prophecy his fulfilled
when other dark siders are destroyed and when she destroys the last of
the sith as she is the chosen one reincarnated. What do you think? I
think this would be better than what we got.

snippet.textDisplay:
It was a movie, salvaged as best as it could be. Alot really made sense as much as many would refuse agree, some other things was vague. It was topped of with a little brainless agenda, like a spoiled cherry on top of a otherwise great icecream sunday. I don't think the ending could have satisfied everyone, or for the biggest part anyone. Life and stories nevee go the way we'd expect, it's never about the end or beginning,it's about the journey that matters most. The story was too big and sentimental for the older audience to agree with its direction in closing, it seemed a bit lost and all over the place for the younger generation. I think it's a case of a story getting dragged out too long for it's own good.

Should this story been finished this way? Nope, not in the eyes of many, but I accept it because it was just a story. Was it a coherently made film? Somewhat, hints of the Emperor returning and other things was pepperd throughout 9 films. Should Disney have just stuck to a new story all together and kept the extended universe cannon? Absolutely, but they didn't, and it is what it is. The story is now told. Time to move on to better things and stop crying because a fictional story didn't go how you wanted it to.

Hopefully the next films will be passed off to a more grounded director, and better writers. The guy doing Mandalorian would be the best to carry the torch. Mabey the Jedi will rise again, and the two swords willl rise from the sands when the Jedi are needed again. Maybe the next triogy will be about the clone of Yoda, a more worthy Jedi taking up the mantle.

Baby Yoda would likely agree.

snippet.textDisplay:
I actually quite like the Force Heal aspect of the movie. I made the connection quickly that she'd learned it by reading the ancient Jedi texts she got from the tree.
When Palpatine sucks the life force from Ben and Rey I thought it was a totally awesome yin-yang moment between Jedi and Sith.
Jedi created a technique to heal, whereas Sith found a way to use the exact same power and take life to heal themselves.
Light Side give, Dark Side take.


A little thing but super neat.


Otherwise there are some serious issues throughout the movie but even I'll admit I left the cinema pleasantly surprised by how much I enjoyed it. Not a good movie but it hit a lot of the right notes: Oscar Isaac and Adam Driver act their asses off and drive the whole thing forward. Kylo's whole ark is the only consistently interesting and well executed one in the whole trilogy. Oscar Isaac is just so charming and fun I couldn't help but love Poe's story here.

snippet.textDisplay: I’ll just say it I think Star Wars fans ruined this sequel trilogy. The Force Awakens comes out and most people love it and it clearly has plans for the future. But some fans start talking about how they hate that The Force Awakens repeats A New Hope. Disney then decides to pull the plug on JJs Star Wars and let Rian do whatever on The Last Jedi so fans don’t complain about similarities with past films and it doesn’t go right either. Some people like they subverted expectations but the majority of Star Wars are greatly disappointed by The Last Jedi. The Rise Of Skywalker was just in a bad situation. The Force Awakens was great set up for this trilogy but The Last Jedi just ruined everything for the future of Star Wars.

snippet.textDisplay:
The movie was all “ Hey guess what!? Nah ya gotta guess... here it is never mind “....
Then they still fucking set up questions. “ Rey I gotta tell you something “ Finn. We will never know... Where was Matt Smith and his very important role? Guess they cut him. Throughout the film I just kept thinking. Oh! Smith will show up now. Oh wait he’s one of the Knights of Ren.... oh wait he’ll turn into young Palpatine.... oh wait... he’s not here.
Kylo shouldn’t have died. Should’ve survived and turned good, but then decides that he has to leave. He’s a criminal and needs to balance his light and dark side.... but NOPE!!! He dies but doesn’t become a force ghost? Maybe a set up for his return? Idk this movie sucks, TLJ sucks and TFA because of the other 2, becomes shitty.
I’m not gonna remember Disney Star Wars in T minus 1 day. 😔
